<h5>
    Negative Acceleration
</h5>

<p class = 'definition'>
    Acceleration can be either positive or negative.
    When it is positive, it means something is speeding up.
    When it is negative, it means something is slowing down.
    Sometimes, negative acceleration is called <emph>deceleration</emph>,
    but most physicists  prefer the term <strong>negative acceleration</strong>.
</p>

